f_{A}(a)=1
0<a<1
f_{X,A=a}(x)=\frac{1}{2a}
-a<x<a
f_{A,X}(a,x)=\frac{1}{2a}
0<a<1
-a<x<a
f_{X}(x)
f_{X}(x)=\int_0^1 f_{A,X}(a,x) da=\int_0^1 \frac{1}{2a}da
-1<x<1
[-a<x<a]
|x|<a<1
     f_X(x) = \int_0^1 f_{A,X}(a,x) \mathrm{d}a = \int_0^1 \frac{1}{2a} [-a<x<a] \mathrm{d}x 
    f_X(x) = \int_{|x|}^a \frac{\mathrm{d}a}{2a} = \frac{1}{2} \ln \frac{1}{|x|} 
